This discarded content discusses a state-of-the-art method to classify GitHub issue reports into their respective categories (bug, enhancement, and question) using a transformer-based model called RoBERTa. The approach was evaluated on approximately 55,000 issue reports across 55 popular languages and achieves promising F-1 scores. The approach aims to address the challenges faced in labeling issue reports and has immediate benefits for the industry, such as effective tracking of issue reports, efficient development documentation, and optimized resource allocation.

data.content:
Automatic Issue Classifier: A Transfer Learning Framework for Classifying Issue Reports
This research paper presents a transformer-based approach for classifying GitHub issue reports in a multi-label setting. The authors use RoBERTa to train their model and achieve promising results with an F1-Score nearing 80%. They also developed and released a tool, Automatic Issue Classifier (AIC), on top of their transfer-based approach.
